  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NFI and Shelter Humanitarian assistance in Kasai</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will ensure that more than 90% of the 630 targeted households with vulnerability score in NFI 3.8 will decrease to a score of 2, also contribute to reducing the vulnerability of 200 households with vulnerability score in shelter 4.8. These families will receive shelter goods and support in rehabilitation of transitional emergency shelters.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through the provision of NFIs and shelter, the vulnerability score for the most vulnerable households, returnee household and IDPs  will be improved. The dignity of affected people will also be regained as a result of NFI and Shelter distribution.  The Shelter will significantly  contribute to protection of the affected people against bad weather and diseases.. In addition, messaging on peaceful coexistence will have a positive and sustainable impact on the living conditions and social cohesion of the community</narrative>
  </description>
